    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-20T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="860"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d860">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R.–Subs/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Messersmith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-20T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 20, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. Embassy’s telegram No. 65, June 17, noon. Press publishes a Presidential
                    decree dated June 17<note n="26" xml:id="d860fn26">Decree No. 1603, June 17,
                        1940, revising Decree No. 2073 of September 1, 1939; for text, see Pan
                        American Union, Law and Treaty Series No. 15, p. 1, or <hi rend="italic"
                            >Official Gazette</hi>, June 21, 1940.</note> excluding belligerent
                    submarines identical with the provisions on that subject contained in the
                    President’s Proclamation of November 4.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
